  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Global Enforcement:\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n- Sharing of financial intelligence\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Sanctions against non-compliant jurisdictions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different financial sectors and jurisdictions.",
